Dozens of mourners thronged the sleepy Kairi village in Gilgil to bid farewell to Monica Kimani whose cruel murder in the Capital city last week left the nation shocked. People lined up on the road side as Ms Kimani's funeral convoy snaked it's way to her ancestral home. Speakers attending the burial condemned her killing and called on investigation agencies to expedite the probe. Though a representative, Gilgil MP Martha Wangari, echoed similar sentiments, saying those involved in the killing should be brought to book.         How phone records exposed Joseph Irungu Kuria.